      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;if-the-automatic-adguard-home-update-fails&#34;&gt;If the automatic AdGuard Home update fails&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this post, ‘&lt;strong&gt;Update AdGuard Home manually&lt;/strong&gt;’, and the accompanying video tutorial, I will show you how to perform a manual update on an AdGuard Home instance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;why-update-adguard-home-manually&#34;&gt;Why update AdGuard Home manually?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some AdGuard Home updates fail to update automatically, for example, version “&lt;strong&gt;AdGuard Home v0.107.17&lt;/strong&gt;.” Therefore, it is necessary to perform a manual update via the command line.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;video-tutorial-on-updating-adguard-home-manually&#34;&gt;Video tutorial on ‘Updating AdGuard Home manually’&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I have also published a video tutorial on my &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/@secure_bits&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;YouTube channel&lt;/a&gt;.
In this video, I show you step by step how to perform a manual update on a Linux-based AdGuard Home installation.
