      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;protect-your-network-from-ads-and-trackers-with-adguard&#34;&gt;Protect your network from ads and trackers with AdGuard&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In today&amp;rsquo;s tutorial, ‘&lt;strong&gt;AdGuard Raspberry Pi Installation&lt;/strong&gt;’, I would like to show you how to install the &lt;strong&gt;AdGuard DNS server&lt;/strong&gt; on a &lt;strong&gt;Raspberry Pi version 3 or higher&lt;/strong&gt;.
With this DNS server, similar to the pihole DNS server (&lt;a href=&#34;https://secure-bits.org/pi-hole-auf-einen-raspberry-pi-installieren/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;click here for the tutorial&lt;/a&gt;), you can ban most ads and data trackers from your home network.
If you still need hardware for your AdGuard DNS server, take a look at the end of this post. I&amp;rsquo;ve put together a short list there.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
